Light/Shadow Effects System

The light/shadow effects system provides a way to create glowing and shadowy objects
in SneezyMUD. This system affects both visibility and light levels in the game.

CREATING OBJECTS WITH LIGHT EFFECTS:

When creating objects, you can use the following flags:
- glow: Makes an object emit light (positive light value)
- shadowy: Makes an object absorb light (negative light value)

Examples:
  @create sword magical glow
  @create dagger magical shadowy

LIGHT EFFECT PROPERTIES:

1. Glowing Objects (positive light value):
   - Are more visible (decreased canBeSeen value)
   - Contribute light to the environment
   - Have the ITEM_GLOW flag set

2. Shadowy Objects (negative light value):
   - Are less visible (increased canBeSeen value)
   - Absorb light from the environment
   - Have the ITEM_SHADOWY flag set

3. Normal Objects (zero light value):
   - Have normal visibility
   - Do not affect light levels
   - Have neither ITEM_GLOW nor ITEM_SHADOWY flags set

NOTES:

- Objects cannot have both glow and shadow effects simultaneously.
- The light effect value is calculated based on the object's volume.
- Larger objects have stronger light/shadow effects.
- The light effect can be viewed using the @stat command.

